      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-07-30</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-09-02T17:16:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Stopping COVID Scams Act of 2020</b><br> <br> This bill provides the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) authority to prohibit unfair or deceptive commercial practices associated with the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) public health emergency. In prohibiting such practices, the FTC must consider whether the practice (1) involves goods or services explicitly advertised as related to the COVID-19 emergency, (2) involves goods or services for which consumer demand significantly increased shortly before or during the emergency, or (3) relates to the federal or state response to the emergency. <br> <br> The bill further specifies procedures for the FTC and the states to enforce such prohibitions.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
